	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Security personnel managed to foil an attempted cash-in-transit heist in KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday following a shootout with robbers, police said. "A security vehicle with three occupants was transporting money from Dundee to Nquthu when they were attacked by a group of unknown men who fired shots at the cash-in-transit vehicle, forcing the truck to leave the road," Brigadier Vish Naidoo said. ALSO READ: 3 security guards injured in Cape Town cash-in-transit heist Naidoo said a fierce gun battle ensued. "The suspects fled the scene in two vehicles, a white Hilux Toyota and a white Audi, which was later found abandoned along [the] Helpmekaar gravel road." Naidoo said there were no reports of injuries.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  